  "prompt": "Which is the best institute in India for doing a hands on course in ethical hacking?",
  "response": "There are several reputable institutes in India that offer hands-on courses in ethical hacking. The best choice can depend on factors such as the course content, duration, faculty, hands-on experience, and placement support. Here are some of the top institutes known for their ethical hacking courses:\n\n1. **Indian Institute of Hardware Technology (IIHT)**: Offers a comprehensive ethical hacking course with practical training.\n\n2. **Netaji Subhas Institute of Technology (NSIT)**: Offers courses in ethical hacking and cybersecurity with industry-relevant training.\n\n3. **EC-Council (Certified Ethical Hacker)**: While not an institute per se, EC-Council certifications are widely recognized, and they have authorized training centers in India.\n\n4. **Techdefence**: Known for its specialized training in ethical hacking and cybersecurity.\n\n5. **ATC (Advanced Technical Center)**: Offers various courses in ethical hacking with an emphasis on practical knowledge.\n\n6. **Delhi School of Internet Marketing (DSIM)**: They provide training in ethical hacking along with digital marketing courses.\n\n7. **Appin Technology Lab**: Offers a range of courses in cybersecurity, including ethical hacking.\n\n8. **Simplilearn**: Provides online courses in ethical hacking, which can be beneficial if you're looking for flexibility.\n\nBefore choosing an institute, it's advisable to check their curriculum, course reviews, faculty experience, and whether they provide practical labs. Additionally, you may want to reach out to alumni for feedback on their experiences.",
